The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 London, June 4: Shareholders in Luxembourg-based Arcelor have succeeded in persuading the company to disclose detailed valuation reports of assets owned by Severstal, the Russian steel group it has agreed to acquire in a 13-billion-euros deal. The documentation will be disclosed in the next two weeks after mounting fears that Arcelor overpaid for its Russian rival as a last-ditch attempt to ward off a hostile takeover bid by Mittal Steel. 

 New Delhi, June 4: Two-wheeler sales growth accelerated in May with Hero Honda, Bajaj Auto and TVS Motor collectively selling nearly 6.27 lakh vehicles, up 26.4 per cent over the year-ago period.

 Calcutta, June 4: The raw materials division of Steel Authority of India Ltd has lined up an investment of over Rs 3,000 crore to increase its iron ore production from 15 million tonnes to 25 million tonnes by 2012 to meet its enhanced requirement.

 Mumbai, June 4: Godrej Consumer Products Ltd is looking at merger and acquisition opportunities in West Asia, Far East and Latin American countries to strengthen its position in the hair colour segment. The company has earmarked an investment of Rs 10 crore to manufacture hair colour at its factory coming up in Sikkim.

 New Delhi, June 4: The NCAER has suggested that the lack of appropriate regulatory mechanism in infrastructure has been a major drawback in attracting private investments for successful public-private partnerships.




